# <type>: <subject>
#
# <body>
#
# <footer>
#
# --- Commit Types ---
# feat:     A new feature
# fix:      A bug fix
# docs:     Documentation changes only
# style:    Code style (formatting, semicolons, etc; no logic change)
# refactor: Code change that neither fixes a bug nor adds a feature
# perf:     Performance improvement
# test:     Adding or updating tests
# build:    Build system or external dependency changes
# ci:       CI configuration changes
# chore:    Other changes that don't modify src or test files
# revert:   Reverts a previous commit
#
# --- Rules ---
# - Subject line: imperative mood, lowercase, no period, max 50 chars
# - Body: explain *what* and *why*, wrap at 72 chars
# - Footer: references (Closes #123) or BREAKING CHANGE notes
# - Blank line between subject, body, and footer
